and yet we serve it on an empty stomach.

586
00:34:43,200 --> 00:34:45,000
The soldiers died
because they were unarmed.

587
00:34:45,320 --> 00:34:45,920
What are you doing?

588
00:34:46,320 --> 00:34:47,040
What are you doing?

589
00:34:48,320 --> 00:34:49,760
This is rebellion!

590
00:34:54,840 --> 00:34:55,640
Hand them over!

591
00:34:57,720 --> 00:34:58,360
Beat him to death!

592
00:35:05,280 --> 00:35:05,680
Tai.

593
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:07,800
Tai, wake up. Don't scare me.

594
00:35:08,240 --> 00:35:08,800
It's okay.

595
00:35:09,720 --> 00:35:10,600
Given his size,

596
00:35:11,000 --> 00:35:12,040
two days of sleep will be enough.

597
00:35:13,040 --> 00:35:14,240
Thank you, Magistrate Di.

598
00:35:18,480 --> 00:35:19,600
With these materials,

599
00:35:20,160 --> 00:35:21,600
you can update your weapons and armor.

600
00:35:22,080 --> 00:35:23,000
Not just the materials.

601
00:35:23,720 --> 00:35:24,960
You helped us get our dignity back.

602
00:35:25,520 --> 00:35:26,360
There is one more thing.

603
00:35:30,640 --> 00:35:31,480
Those child soldiers

604
00:35:32,680 --> 00:35:33,760
were wronged and driven to death.

605
00:35:35,280 --> 00:35:36,440
They were 14 years old or so.

606
00:35:37,600 --> 00:35:38,800
Harsh military discipline

607
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:40,280
stifled their instincts,

608
00:35:40,720 --> 00:35:41,760
achieving the opposite effect.

609
00:35:43,200 --> 00:35:45,120
They got caught up in a storm

610
00:35:46,520 --> 00:35:47,880
and died for nothing.

611
00:35:49,360 --> 00:35:50,040
It's a pity.

612
00:35:51,640 --> 00:35:52,280
It's lamentable.

613
00:35:59,360 --> 00:35:59,960
Leaving.

614
00:36:10,100 --> 00:36:12,120
[Penglai County Magistrate's Office]

615
00:36:12,120 --> 00:36:12,710
Mr. Hong,

616
00:36:13,840 --> 00:36:15,440
yesterday I was sorting
through the fellows' belongings.

617
00:36:16,320 --> 00:36:17,560
I discovered this.

618
00:36:18,670 --> 00:36:19,400
I was in a hurry to bring it here.

619
00:36:19,520 --> 00:36:21,360
[Pawn Ticket]
I don't know if it is useful to you.

620
00:36:22,040 --> 00:36:22,710
Pawn ticket?

621
00:36:23,600 --> 00:36:24,710
This is the client's stub.

622
00:36:26,000 --> 00:36:27,150
They must have recently pawned something

623
00:36:27,630 --> 00:36:29,120
at Zhong's Pawn Shop.

624
00:36:29,840 --> 00:36:30,600
Thank you.

625
00:36:40,400 --> 00:36:41,400
Magistrate,

626
00:36:42,280 --> 00:36:44,800
I've been hiding something from you.

627
00:36:45,320 --> 00:36:46,840
I knew you as Qiao Tai

628
00:36:47,320 --> 00:36:48,840
from way back.

629
00:36:50,280 --> 00:36:51,680
You are my assistant.

630
00:36:52,480 --> 00:36:53,520
Don't mention

631
00:36:54,640 --> 00:36:55,200
the past again.

632
00:36:56,600 --> 00:36:58,560
Magistrate, Mr. Hong wants to see you.

633
00:37:01,800 --> 00:37:02,320
Don't mention it.

634
00:37:09,440 --> 00:37:10,640
Tai, don't worry.

635
00:37:10,920 --> 00:37:13,120
I didn't tell Magistrate
about your embarrassing things.

636
00:37:13,880 --> 00:37:14,880
I told him

637
00:37:15,320 --> 00:37:17,080
you went into battle

638
00:37:17,400 --> 00:37:18,520
and killed the enemies bravely.

639
00:37:18,600 --> 00:37:19,160
However,

640
00:37:19,240 --> 00:37:20,160
you met a treacherous person

641
00:37:20,200 --> 00:37:21,480
and were harmed by him.

642
00:37:22,080 --> 00:37:22,600
But

643
00:37:22,840 --> 00:37:25,680
you still put up a strong fight.

644
00:37:26,600 --> 00:37:27,480
Did Magistrate believe it?

645
00:37:27,480 --> 00:37:28,160
Ma Rong.

646
00:37:34,800 --> 00:37:36,040
[Pawn Ticket]
Fortunately, I arrived in time.

647
00:37:36,560 --> 00:37:37,120
Otherwise,

648
00:37:37,480 --> 00:37:38,360
it would be too late.

649
00:37:39,240 --> 00:37:40,120
That's right.

650
00:37:40,200 --> 00:37:42,280
My heart was in my throat at that time.

651
00:37:42,560 --> 00:37:44,560
Fortunately, Magistrate bought us time.

652
00:37:45,880 --> 00:37:47,080
There are so many documents.

653
00:37:47,080 --> 00:37:48,120
How did you recite them all?

654
00:37:48,640 --> 00:37:49,800
There are so many documents.

655
00:37:50,080 --> 00:37:51,800
I can't recite them all.

656
00:37:53,000 --> 00:37:54,240
So you...

657
00:37:54,240 --> 00:37:55,480
So I made it up.

658
00:38:00,160 --> 00:38:01,080
Speaking of solving the case,

659
00:38:01,840 --> 00:38:03,480
now Ying'er and the eighth camp

660
00:38:03,480 --> 00:38:04,600
are cleared now.

661
00:38:05,320 --> 00:38:06,120
This case

662
00:38:07,160 --> 00:38:08,400
might have to return
to the starting point

663
00:38:08,720 --> 00:38:09,880
and be re-investigated.

664
00:38:10,360 --> 00:38:11,280
Perhaps

665
00:38:11,920 --> 00:38:13,440
the child soldiers from the eighth camp

666
00:38:14,160 --> 00:38:15,920
showed me a new direction.

667
00:38:17,040 --> 00:38:18,600
I won't believe you from now on.

668
00:38:19,280 --> 00:38:20,560
There's not a word of truth
in your mouth.

669
00:38:34,160 --> 00:38:34,680
Miss Cao.

670
00:38:35,200 --> 00:38:36,400
Why are you so flustered?

671
00:38:36,640 --> 00:38:37,400
What happened?

672
00:38:37,760 --> 00:38:38,760
I went past the market just now.

673
00:38:38,920 --> 00:38:40,320
I heard the discussions
among the merchants.

674
00:38:40,600 --> 00:38:41,160
They said

675
00:38:41,200 --> 00:38:42,280
Magistrate Di encountered a big trouble

676
00:38:42,280 --> 00:38:43,280
in the military camp.

677
00:38:43,360 --> 00:38:44,600
We are not sure about his safety now.

678
00:38:46,280 --> 00:38:47,200
They also saw Mr. Hong

679
00:38:47,200 --> 00:38:48,680
escorting the owner of Xie's Salt Shop

680
00:38:48,720 --> 00:38:50,320
to the military camp aggressively.

681
00:38:50,640 --> 00:38:53,600
It is said he was going
to save Magistrate Di.

682
00:38:56,600 --> 00:38:57,040
Okay.

683
00:38:57,640 --> 00:38:58,320
I got it.

684
00:39:01,280 --> 00:39:02,600
According to your instructions,

685
00:39:02,600 --> 00:39:04,600
I told Miss Cao about this.

686
00:39:05,000 --> 00:39:05,400
But

687
00:39:05,800 --> 00:39:07,440
she didn't seem to be responding.

688
00:39:08,280 --> 00:39:09,000
Really?

689
00:39:20,640 --> 00:39:22,320
She wasn't like this just now.

690
00:39:26,640 --> 00:39:28,000
One's feelings

691
00:39:28,320 --> 00:39:29,320
can deceive others

692
00:39:29,560 --> 00:39:31,000
but not oneself.

693
00:39:32,320 --> 00:39:33,000
Xiang,

694
00:39:33,720 --> 00:39:35,120
write up some new recruits

695
00:39:35,120 --> 00:39:37,520
on the music house's behalf
and put them up.

696
00:39:38,400 --> 00:39:40,680
We need to recruit new people.

697
00:39:42,740 --> 00:39:48,980
[Penglai County Magistrate's Office]

698
00:40:32,440 --> 00:40:33,280
How is it?

699
00:40:34,040 --> 00:40:35,680
My skills haven't

700
00:40:35,920 --> 00:40:37,800
deteriorated too much, have they?

701
00:40:38,680 --> 00:40:39,560
Not at all.

702
00:40:41,440 --> 00:40:42,760
I can't remember

703
00:40:43,440 --> 00:40:44,840
the last time

704
00:40:45,520 --> 00:40:47,000
I heard you play.

705
00:40:50,200 --> 00:40:51,520
You are about to leave.

706
00:40:51,920 --> 00:40:54,520
My Mingyue House will lose
the leading musician.

707
00:40:55,200 --> 00:40:57,720
I can't find a better one
in a short time.

708
00:40:58,080 --> 00:41:00,240
So I have to practice myself.

709
00:41:01,280 --> 00:41:02,760
Did I say I would leave?

710
00:41:04,960 --> 00:41:06,440
Then write me a guarantee.

711
00:41:07,000 --> 00:41:08,040
Promise me that you won't leave.

712
00:41:10,760 --> 00:41:11,400
Well...

713
00:41:12,920 --> 00:41:13,600
Look,

714
00:41:14,200 --> 00:41:15,480
you just won't admit your feelings.

715
00:41:16,160 --> 00:41:17,520
You can't hide

716
00:41:17,760 --> 00:41:18,920
your feelings for a man.

717
00:41:19,640 --> 00:41:21,240
As for your concerns,

718
00:41:21,800 --> 00:41:23,120
they are not actually concerns.

719
00:41:25,880 --> 00:41:26,800
You know it again?

720
00:41:27,760 --> 00:41:28,960
I've known it long ago.

721
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:31,160
Don't worry

722
00:41:31,200 --> 00:41:32,200
about what you can't keep.

723
00:41:33,280 --> 00:41:34,800
Can't rely on others.

724
00:41:35,560 --> 00:41:36,200
I have to

725
00:41:36,240 --> 00:41:37,880
rely on myself.

726
00:41:40,120 --> 00:41:41,520
I might as well go
and practice my instrument.

